Use `if` when code should run only under one condition.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    if ready:
        io.line("Ready!")
    ;
]

Add `else` for the other path:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    if ready:
        io.line("Ready!")
    else
        io.line("Not ready yet")
    ;
]

One semicolon closes the whole structure.

Beanstalk does not have an `else if` chain. Nest another `if` inside `else`, or
use pattern matching when several cases belong to one value.
